definition.value: A  bisabolene that is cyclohexene substituted by a methyl group at position 1 and a 6-methylhepta-1,5-dien-2-yl group at position 4.
An optically active 9-(phosphonooxy)-10-hydroxy derivative of stearic acid with (9S,10S)-configuration.
A 9,10-dihydroxyoctadecanoic acid diastereoisomer in which both stereocentres have S configuration.
The conjugate base of (R)-3-hydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxopentanoic acid and R enantiomer of 3-hydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxopentanoate.
An N-acyl-gamma-aminobutyric acid resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of 4-aminobutanoic acid with the gamma-carbxy group of L-glutamic acid.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxycyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carboxylic acid.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is 3-oxochola-4,6-dien-24-oic acid carrying an additional hydroxy group at the 12alpha-position.
